unrest

34
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:43,750
over economic struggles.”

35
00:01:43,750 --> 00:01:46,100
What’s different about these protests—

36
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:48,480
compared to the big ones in 2009—

37
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:49,820
is that they aren’t targeted

38
00:01:49,820 --> 00:01:52,479
at any particular political faction.

39
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:55,579
They’re against the entire system.

40
00:01:55,579 --> 00:01:59,799
Here are protestors shouting “Mullahs, get
lost.”

41
00:01:59,799 --> 00:02:02,140
In Iran, mullahs are the religious leaders

42
00:02:02,140 --> 00:02:03,950
who control the government.

43
00:02:03,950 --> 00:02:05,670
In another city, the protesters shout

44
00:02:05,670 --> 00:02:09,680
“This is a bloody month, the mullahs are
falling.”

45
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,150
And in this video,

46
00:02:11,150 --> 00:02:13,050
protesters are rejecting their government’s

47
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:14,260
anti-American propaganda,

48
00:02:14,260 --> 00:02:17,060
