under threat of US sanctions.

62
00:02:54,510 --> 00:02:58,100
So the Chinese regime has been stepping in
to buy it up.

63
00:02:58,100 --> 00:02:59,360
And at the same time,

64
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:02,580
cheap Chinese goods are flooding into Iran.

65
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:04,800
So China is filling the gaps left behind

66
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:07,100
by countries that are retreating.

67
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:09,190
China is now Iran’s biggest trading partner

68
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:11,600
and has traditionally relied on Iran’s oil

69
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:15,010
to fuel economic growth both inside China,

70
00:03:15,010 --> 00:03:16,201
and as part of the Belt and Road Initiative.

71
00:03:16,201 --> 00:03:21,370
In 2017, China imported a third of all Iranian
oil,

72
00:03:21,370 --> 00:03:23,180
more than any other country.

73
00:03:23,180 --> 00:03:26,160
So when a French energy giant called Total

74
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:28,100
succumbed to US pressure,

75
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:30,200
and pulled out of a 5 billion dollar agreement

76
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:34,750
